      "revision": 1,
      "revision_notes": "Round 1 revisions complete; addressed all 4 HIGH (SA-H1 lastConfirmedOrder seed-on-load + lastOptimisticByTable comparison; SA-H2 column-level intersection overwrite check; SA-H3 ack defers applyServerOrder until queue empty; SA-H4 single reconcileAfterDrop entry-point) + 3 MEDIUM (SA-M1 useLayoutEffect; SA-M2 ack-vs-broadcast ordering test added; SA-M3 queue-full guard moved to handleDragStart) + 2 LOW (SA-L1 RBAC stub note; SA-L2 websocket-events.md doc task) findings from Apollo's spec-review-sa.md.",
      "started": "2026-04-30T15:25:30+08:00",
      "status": "complete",
      "summary": "v2 (revised after Apollo SA review): Uses @dnd-kit/core+sortable behind React Flow's nodrag/nowheel pattern (Spike S1 PASS) with explicit useUpdateNodeInternals(tableId) via useLayoutEffect for AC-05d-compliant edge re-anchoring (Spike S2 + SA-M1). Adds new column:reorder/column:reordered/column:reorder:ack WebSocket protocol with single Prisma transaction batch update, server-side FM-07 merge, and per-table FIFO queue (≤5) gated at handleDragStart (SA-M3). Drop reconciliation goes through a single reconcileAfterDrop entry-point (SA-H4) that runs the column-level overwrite check (SA-H2) and applies buffered remote on no-op drops (AC-14f). Ack handling defers applyServerOrder until queue empty to prevent in-flight snap-back (SA-H3). Sync-reconcile compares server vs. lastOptimisticByTable and fires AC-08e/f toast when dirty, with lastConfirmedOrder seeded from initial whiteboard load to handle first-ever-reorder loss (SA-H1). 7 files to create, 7 to modify (added websocket-events.md per SA-L2), 3 dependencies added; no DB migration needed."
